body:
@LukeAI ah ok, if you already have labels for 4 coordinates, then all you need to do is transform your labels into xywh angle format.

The detection layer modifications are simply expanding the output channels by 1 per anchor, and adding a loss component for angle.

Plotting the results would be more work of course, and you'd probably need to work out some sort of angle-iou function if you wanted to get a proper mAP, but training only requires the 3 steps above.

@duyao-art you are conflating two completely seperate topics. 

xyxy or xywh are simply two different representations of the same data, and we have functions in utils.utils to transform both back and forth.

The **_units_** of the boxes are completely independent of their representation, i.e. they may be pixels, or normalized, or grid units etc.
